NOTE: useful when you're scanning UI code

Step 1: Install SonarScanner CLI on your server

Download the latest SonarScanner CLI:
cd /opt
sudo wget https://binaries.sonarsource.com/Distribution/sonar-scanner-cli/sonar-scanner-cli-5.0.1.3006-linux.zip
sudo unzip sonar-scanner-cli-5.0.1.3006-linux.zip
sudo mv sonar-scanner-5.0.1.3006-linux sonar-scanner
sudo rm sonar-scanner-cli-5.0.1.3006-linux.zip

Add sonar-scanner to PATH:
echo 'export PATH=$PATH:/opt/sonar-scanner/bin' | sudo tee /etc/profile.d/sonar-scanner.sh
source /etc/profile.d/sonar-scanner.sh


Verify installation:
sonar-scanner -v

OP:
SonarScanner 5.0.1.3006
Java 17
